    "title_en": "Propagation of Dirac spherical waves in the expanding universe",
    "abstract_en": "The explicit formulas for the spherical solutions of the Dirac equation in the expanding universe are given. The initial value of the solution can be, in particular, a wave function of the hydrogen-like atom or a spherical wave in the Minkowski space, that then propagates in the Friedmann-Lemaître-Robertson-Walker space-time, which is expanding with the de~Sitter scale factor.",
